cs.CG, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper analyzes the computational complexity of game mechanics in 3D environments, which involves geometric calculations and spatial reasoning. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper explicitly discusses the computational complexity of the analyzed games, and provides proofs of NP-hardness and PSPACE-completeness. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may be of interest to researchers in AI who are interested in developing intelligent agents that can play video games. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper analyzes the complexity of game mechanics, which is a topic of interest in game theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper provides proofs of computational complexity for specific game mechanics, which involves analyzing the algorithms and data structures used in the game.
